<!--
    MainActivity layout.
    Contains a FrameLayout container for fragments and a BottomNavigationView for navigation.

    Reference List:
    Android Room Database & Data Persistence
    Android Developers (2024) Save data in a local database using Room. Available at: https://developer.android.com/training/data-storage/room (Accessed: 26 April 2026).
    Android Developers (2024) Accessing data using Room DAOs. Available at: https://developer.android.com/training/data-storage/room/accessing-data (Accessed: 26 April 2026).
    Lacerda, D. (2024) Room Database in Android: A comprehensive guide. Available at: https://medium.com/@dlacerda/room-database-in-android-a-comprehensive-guide (Accessed: 26 April 2026).
    Kotlin & Android Development
    Android Developers (2024) Android Basics with Compose. Available at: https://developer.android.com/courses/android-basics-compose/course (Accessed: 26 April 2026).
    Leiva, A. (2023) Kotlin for Android Developers. Victoria, BC: Leanpub.
    JetBrains (2024) Kotlin documentation: Coroutines basics. Available at: https://kotlinlang.org/docs/coroutines-basics.html (Accessed: 26 April 2026).
    MVVM Architecture Pattern
    Android Developers (2024) Guide to app architecture. Available at: https://developer.android.com/topic/architecture (Accessed: 26 April 2026).
    Android Developers (2024) ViewModel overview. Available at: https://developer.android.com/topic/libraries/architecture/viewmodel (Accessed: 26 April 2026).
    Mobile UI/UX Design
    Google (2024) Material Design 3: Design guidelines. Available at: https://m3.material.io/ (Accessed: 26 April 2026).
    Babich, N. (2024) 'Mobile UX design: Key principles', Smashing Magazine. Available at: https://www.smashingmagazine.com/2024/02/mobile-ux-design-key-principles/ (Accessed: 26 April 2026).
    Budget Tracking & Personal Finance
    Sahay, A. (2024) 'The role of mobile applications in personal financial management among young adults', International Journal of Finance and Economics, 29(2), pp. 1045–1062.
    Pew Research Center (2024) Mobile technology and home broadband 2024. Available at: https://www.pewresearch.org/internet/2024/01/31/mobile-technology-and-home-broadband-2024/ (Accessed: 26 April 2026).
    Camera & Image Handling in Android
    Android Developers (2024) Take photos. Available at: https://developer.android.com/media/camera/camera-deprecated/photobasics (Accessed: 26 April 2026).
    Android Developers (2024) FileProvider. Available at: https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/core/content/FileProvider (Accessed: 26 April 2026).
-->
<LinearLayout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android" xmlns:app="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res-auto"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    android:orientation="vertical"
    android:background="@color/background_cream"
    android:fitsSystemWindows="true">

    <!-- Container where the fragments are loaded -->
    <FrameLayout android:id="@+id/fragmentContainer"
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="0dp"
        android:layout_weight="1"/>

    <!-- Bottom navigation bar for switching between main features -->
    <com.google.android.material.bottomnavigation.BottomNavigationView
        android:id="@+id/bottomNavigation"
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:background="@android:color/white"
        app:menu="@menu/bottom_nav_menu"
        app:itemIconTint="@color/bottom_nav_color"
        app:itemTextColor="@color/bottom_nav_color"
        app:labelVisibilityMode="labeled"/>
</LinearLayout>
